                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7609: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-09-03T14:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 3—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>372. My 366, September 1, 7 p.m. Following from American consul general at
                    Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Urgent. September 3, 7 a.m. Heavy sustained attack started from Pagoda
                            Hill on Wuchang this morning at 4 o’clock. Heavy artillery, machine-gun
                            and rifle fire plainly heard here and visible. Bombardment still
                            continues but now somewhat reduced. Distance from Pagoda Hill to Wuchang
                            about one mile. Volunteer forces and naval units were called out here at
                            6:40 this morning. Much excitement but as yet no actual trouble reported
                            on this side of river. Will telegraph later.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
